Sentencas: Oxide ion flux at cathode/electrolyte interface of solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) is investigated through quenching reaction and oxygen isotope labeling.
Titulo: Investigation of oxide ion flux at cathode/electrolyte interface in solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: A YSZ (yttria-stabilized zirconia) electrolyte-supported cell with LSM (strontium-doped lanthanum manganite)/YSZ porous cathode is operated by supplying O-18(2) at 973 K and abruptly quenched to room temperature by a direct helium gas-impinging jet to the cell.
Titulo: Investigation of oxide ion flux at cathode/electrolyte interface in solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The O-18 concentration distribution in the cross section of the cathode/electrolyte interface is obtained by secondary ion mass spectrometry (SIMS) with a spatial resolution of 50 nm.
Titulo: Investigation of oxide ion flux at cathode/electrolyte interface in solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: From the analysis of oxygen isotope diffusion profiles in YSZ electrolyte, oxide ion flux incorporated from a cathode/electrolyte interface to an electrolyte is first estimated.
Titulo: Investigation of oxide ion flux at cathode/electrolyte interface in solid oxide fuel cell
